<Author>CarolineF
<Content>Great hotel in good location Stayed at the Fira Palace for 3 nights. Arrived from airport at 12 noon and room was ready for us. Check in was fast and efficient dealt with by friendly staff. Our room was on the 4th floor overlooking the local school and with views towards the Tibadado mountain and castle. Room was very large and very clean with a well stocked bathroom with his  her sinks, separate shower and separate toilet areas. Large wide screen television, but still the only English channels were BBC World News, CNN and sport channel. The bed was a super king size, but although we slept very well (partly due to the excellent black-out curtains and lack of street noise) the mattress was quite hard. Didn't have breakfast which was 16 Euros per person. We took a travel kettle with us and bought juice and croissants locally. Used the hotel pool which was good, but didn't have time to use the gym. The Espanya Metro stop was an easy and pleasant walk from the hotel, being alongside the Magic Fountains (these are not in use from the end of September so we didn't get to see them). Barcelona is a large and busy city, but the Metro is a quick and fairly easy way of getting around. We bought T10 tickets which cost E7.50 and give you 10 journeys per ticket and can also be used on the bus (the No 46 takes you directly to the airport from Pl Espanya). Would recommend a visit to Park Guell (which is free) and also the Olympic complex which is within walking distance of the hotel. We didn't have time to see everything, but managed to see the main places of interest.Having signed up for the 'I Prefer' scheme we were given a free late check-out till 6pm which was greatly appreciated as our flight was not until late and it gave us the whole of the day to look around the city.Would definitely stay at the Fira Palace again. 
