<Content>Fira...nice but a bad taste Stayed here for three nights. Rooms were quite nice...very big, the bathrooms were huge and magnificent (tub, seperate room for toilet and seperate huge shower with jets!). Yes the beds were too hard for my liking, but my spouse didn't mind. The location is fine...it is really only a 5 min walk to one of two metro stations (one the green line, which leads right to las ramblas, and gets you there in less than ten mins) Regarding previous reviews about the location and the metro being hard to navigate, well, they must not metro much. It was very straigtforward and the 2 and 3 days passes are very reasonably priced.We did not eat here....breakfast was not in our rate and the room card said the continental breakfast was 14.95 euros...ridiculous...not a chance.The hotel itself was very nice...what bugged me was the service. We booked early and got a rate of 129 Eur, no breakfast. Two days before we left the listed rates had dropped to 99 Euros including breakfast. I emailed the hotel and requested the new rate. They did not answer my email. When we arrived I discussed this with the front desk, and was told tough luck, too bad, 72 hour cancellation if you don't like it you will be charged half of your three nights at the original rate. So walking out wasn't really an option. With regard to other requests, the front desk staff were not very knowledgeable. The gondola at the waterfront is closed for a while for renovations....after reading something that alluded to this, but hearing the front desk recommend it to another patron we asked. This guy said he didn't know and because it was a holiday, there was no way to find out (from any other staff or any other means). Ok? The last morning the girl on the front desk kindly circled where to catch the airport bus (5 min walk)...too bad it was the wrong place....we spotted the bus stopped around the corner from where she directed us. Oi. To top it all off, arriving home there was an email message from the hotel hoping that we had enjoyed our stay and welcoming and comments or questions. So they will email uselessness in the name of providing the best service, but they won't answer your email if you are asking them to honor the best rate available two days before arrival. My advice, don't book far ahead, or if you do, recheck the rate 73 hours before and if it's much better, cancel and rebook. That would have saved us 90 euros!The hotel rating would have been a 5, the service disappointment dropped it to a 3. 
